commit.message: Merge remote-tracking branch 'kobol/c++11'

replace garbage collector for shared pointers

the old garbage collector prevented the deallocation of the referenced
object in a realtime context, but not that of the shared reference
counter.
the new implementation is extremely simple and not particularly scalable,
but it works and is actually fully realtime safe.

port to C++11

* replace functionality from boost with its C++11 equivalents whenever
  possible. remaining uses of boost are noncopyable, lexical_cast,
  variant, and tokenizer.
* remove das::regex and use std::regex instead.
enable rubberband support by default
remove unused argument / class member
"update" warning flags to -Wall -Wextra
add realtime annotations for use with stoat

honor environment variables

CXX, CXXFLAGS, CPPFLAGS and LDFLAGS.
add .gitignore

slightly nicer error message
